1
00:00:55,359 --> 00:00:56,200
What's going on?

2
00:00:58,439 --> 00:00:59,759
That bastard Sun!

3
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,520
Didn't we agree on a truce tonight?

4
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:07,959
It's the Ghost Soldiers!

5
00:01:08,319 --> 00:01:08,799
Ghost Soldiers?

6
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:25,480
Marshal.

7
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,040
Take a look.

8
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:26,920
Here they come.

9
00:01:27,159 --> 00:01:27,959
They're fighting!

10
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:33,599
What's your name?

11
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:35,079
His name is...

12
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,040
Lao Jiugui.

13
00:01:36,159 --> 00:01:36,680
Good.

14
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:37,719
Lao Jiugui,

15
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,120
I hereby appoint you

16
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,560
Major, Regimental Commander.

17
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:43,840
Quick, thank the Marshal!

18
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,120
Plus ten gold bars.

19
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:48,799
Marshal.

20
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,239
You may go clean up the battlefield.

21
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:54,000
Move out!

22
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:09,400
The Eternal Lamp burns even by day.

23
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,879
That's a lot of oil money over a year.

24
00:02:12,879 --> 00:02:14,800
How many times have I told you?

25
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,199
If this lamp ever goes out,

26
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:19,719
the departed spirits get no guidance,

27
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:21,319
can't enter Reincarnation,

28
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,240
and become...

29
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:23,759
wandering ghosts.

30
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,000
I've followed you for over ten years,

31
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,120
and never seen a single ghost.

32
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:31,120
What do you mean, "followed me for ten years"?

33
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,520
Don't you go disturbing my Daoist heart.

34
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,159
Back then, it was the Mayor

35
00:02:37,159 --> 00:02:38,199
who, to shut me up,

36
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:39,400
handed the Bone-Keeping Temple over to me.

37
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:42,039
And I, seeing you all alone with no one,

38
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,319
young and strong,

39
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:47,759
called you over to look after the two kids.

40
00:02:48,039 --> 00:02:48,719
Isn't that right?

41
00:03:00,199 --> 00:03:02,000
Thank you, Lao Jiugui.

42
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,680
What is it?

43
00:03:11,039 --> 00:03:12,000
I suddenly...

44
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,759
felt a trace of happiness.

45
00:03:17,919 --> 00:03:19,240
My Daoist heart is shaken.

46
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:20,879
I feel something bad...

47
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:21,840
is about to happen.

48
00:03:21,919 --> 00:03:23,080
What are you talking about?

49
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:23,840
Where is he?

50
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,560
Get out here!

51
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,520
Who the hell are you people?

52
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:29,439
Why are you beating him?

53
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,280
Out of respect for Lao Jiugui,

54
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,199
we only beat him up.

55
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:34,919
Otherwise, he'd be at the station already.

56
00:03:34,919 --> 00:03:36,319
Why would you send him to the station?

57
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,520
He cheated.

58
00:03:38,039 --> 00:03:38,639
Any other time,

59
00:03:38,639 --> 00:03:39,960
we'd have chopped off his hands and feet.

60
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,759
Since he owes me gambling debts,

61
00:03:42,759 --> 00:03:43,919
we'll let him off today.

62
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,199
How much does he owe you?

63
00:03:45,879 --> 00:03:48,039
One hundred silver dollars.

64
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:48,840
What?

65
00:03:49,159 --> 00:03:49,879
You're lying!

66
00:03:50,639 --> 00:03:51,879
I only owe you twenty silver dollars.

67
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,080
What kind of interest is that high?

68
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,280
Think it's too much?

69
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,520
Then don't fucking borrow!

70
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,599
Pay up, now.

71
00:03:57,599 --> 00:03:59,719
Paying debts is only right.

72
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,199
But let me tell you,

73
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,080
inside the Bone-Keeping Temple,

74
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,199
only the dead are kept here.

75
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,599
If you keep yelling like this,

76
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,039
you'll disturb the departed spirits,

77
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:10,759
and have bad luck for life.

78
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,400
Hand over the money.

79
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,600
Ruling.

80
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:19,680
Get the money.

81
00:04:26,399 --> 00:04:27,600
I was wrong, Master.

82
00:04:30,279 --> 00:04:31,600
Idling about every day,

83
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,079
your sister is off at university,

84
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:34,959
and look at you.

85
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,720
Now you've picked up a gambling habit too.

86
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:38,240
Master.

87
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,439
I truly know I was wrong.

88
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,279
I'm sorry.

89
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,360
Back in the day,

90
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,920
I never should have taken you in.

91
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,079
I'm sorry.

92
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,079
The boy is still young.

93
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:46,600
Still young?

94
00:04:46,879 --> 00:04:47,639
And what'll he do when he's older?

95
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,120
Tear a hole right through the sky?

96
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:54,399
Give them back their money.

97
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:57,959
It's not enough.

98
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,199
There's only eighty silver dollars.

99
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,879
Not a cent less.

100
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,120
Inside the Bone-Keeping Temple,

101
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,800
besides that Eternal Lamp,

102
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,439
what else do you think is valuable?

103
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:13,480
Take it.

104
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:15,720
That's Lao Jiugui for you.

105
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,199
Always a straight shooter.

106
00:05:28,079 --> 00:05:28,800
Forget it.

107
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:30,920
Let it go.

108
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:37,160
Dongsheng.

109
00:05:37,639 --> 00:05:39,079
Get up and apologize to Master.

110
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,240
Apologize to Master.

111
00:05:43,519 --> 00:05:44,399
Sit down and eat.

112
00:05:44,759 --> 00:05:45,759
Eat what?!

113
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,199
Get out!

114
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,800
From this day on,

115
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,480
don't set foot in the Bone-Keeping Temple again.

116
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:53,240
I can leave,

117
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,199
but...

118
00:05:55,959 --> 00:05:56,800
can you tell me,

119
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,720
who killed my mother?

120
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:05,600
Get out!

121
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:27,839
Dongsheng.

122
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,199
Dongsheng.

123
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:30,759
Lao Jiugui, what's wrong with you?

124
00:06:30,759 --> 00:06:31,879
Say one more word,

125
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:33,720
and you can get out too.

126
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,120
Out!

127
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:52,639
Get out!

128
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:01,759
Well, if it isn't...

129
00:07:01,759 --> 00:07:03,439
the young master of the Bone-Keeping Temple.

130
00:07:03,759 --> 00:07:04,240
What?

131
00:07:04,399 --> 00:07:05,600
Back to play a few hands?

132
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,600
Play?

133
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:09,199
Even a dog wouldn't play with you.

134
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,319
Wake up!

135
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:25,000
Wake up!

136
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,480
What is it?

137
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,319
You wanna sleep?

138
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:28,439
You'll have to sleep somewhere else.

139
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:30,360
We're recruiting soldiers here.

140
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:32,600
Lend a hand.

141
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,680
With a build like yours,

142
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,600
it'd be a waste not to enlist.

143
00:07:41,959 --> 00:07:42,680
You mean me?

144
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,360
I'd rather starve to death

145
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,079
than become a soldier.

146
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:46,959
Why?

147
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,639
These days,

148
00:07:48,839 --> 00:07:49,839
anyone with a couple of guns

149
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,120
dares to call himself a Marshal.

150
00:07:51,959 --> 00:07:53,439
You're talking about the old warlords.

151
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:54,560
Our Brigade Commander is different.

152
00:07:54,959 --> 00:07:56,000
Same wine, different bottle.

153
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,160
My Master said it himself.

154
00:07:57,639 --> 00:07:58,199
Today,

155
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,360
either Warlord Zhang fights Warlord Wang,

156
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,720
or Warlord Wang fights Warlord Li.

157
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:02,000
Your Master was a soldier too?

158
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,720
A mere soldier? Please.

159
00:08:03,879 --> 00:08:04,519
My Master was a

160
00:08:04,519 --> 00:08:05,560
Colonel, Regiment Commander.

161
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:08,160
Steamed buns!

162
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,319
Hot steamed buns!

163
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:13,439
Do soldiers get fed?

164
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:17,959
Have a bite first.

165
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,240
Flatbread!

166
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,519
Slow down.

167
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,360
No one's gonna fight you for it.

168
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,159
Eat slowly.

169
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:46,279
By the way,

170
00:08:46,679 --> 00:08:47,399
What's your name?

171
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:48,240
Shuisheng.

172
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:49,960
Shuisheng?

173
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:51,600
Born in the water.

174
00:08:57,919 --> 00:08:59,120
That's the Mayor's car.

175
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:00,919
Looks like over these years,

176
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,000
the Mayor's been pocketing plenty.

177
00:09:07,519 --> 00:09:08,279
Qiuying!

178
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,080
Somebody!

179
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,000
Quick, put her on the bed.

180
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,279
Brother.

181
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:30,919
Who are you?

182
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:33,240
Director Sun.

183
00:09:33,559 --> 00:09:34,559
A busy man like you forgets easily.

184
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,840
I'm Brigade Commander Li Chuanzhong's

185
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,399
Orderly.

186
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:37,919
Last time the Mayor came with you

187
00:09:37,919 --> 00:09:38,679
to our Commander's residence,

188
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:39,360
we met.

189
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:41,639
Look at me.

190
00:09:41,639 --> 00:09:42,639
So busy I forgot.

191
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,480
Lord Beile.

192
00:09:49,639 --> 00:09:50,440
The young lady's illness...

193
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:50,759
I...

194
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,039
I can't treat it.

195
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:53,879
You damn useless fool!

196
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,320
Lord Beile, I really can't treat it.

197
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:59,240
This isn't an illness at all.

198
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:02,399
No clinic will be of any use.

199
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:07,440
You two.

200
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,440
Who are you, then?

201
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,039
Well,

202
00:10:11,279 --> 00:10:11,799
Lord Beile,

203
00:10:11,879 --> 00:10:12,320
Let me

204
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,759
introduce them to you.

205
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:14,679
These two

206
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:16,600
are famous Spirit Mediums from Manchuria.

207
00:10:17,399 --> 00:10:18,720
And today they

208
00:10:18,759 --> 00:10:19,759
happened to wander by my place.

209
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:21,559
Since the great masters have spoken,

210
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:22,360
then the young lady

211
00:10:22,679 --> 00:10:24,320
can definitely be saved.

212
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:26,120
You say it's not an illness.

213
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,159
Then what is it?

214
00:10:35,879 --> 00:10:36,360
This...

215
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:38,039
She's Possessed!

216
00:10:38,039 --> 00:10:38,960
Impossible.

217
00:10:40,799 --> 00:10:42,879
Your young lady...

218
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:44,320
recently, did she

219
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,799
encounter Something unclean?

220
00:10:46,879 --> 00:10:47,840
Impossible.

221
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:49,559
She's the Mayor's daughter.

222
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,279
She's never lifted a finger.

223
00:10:51,639 --> 00:10:53,240
The servants do all the dirty work.

224
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:54,720
What they mean is,

225
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:55,320
has the young lady

226
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,600
encountered any Demons and monsters?

227
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,399
How would I know that?

228
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,399
But,

229
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,080
this morning,

230
00:11:03,879 --> 00:11:05,240
my sister and brother-in-law

231
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,840
did go to the temple to burn incense.
